sworth| title = A History of English Law Volume IV (7th edition)| publisher = Methuen| location = London| year = 1956| isbn = 978-0-42105-040-2}}\n* {{cite book| first = E. H.| last = Jenkins| title = A History of the French Navy| publisher = McDonald and Jayne\u2019s| location = London| year = 1973| isbn = 978-0-35604-196-4}}\n* {{cite book| first = F. M.| last = Kert| title = Prize and Prejudice: Privateering and Naval Prize in Atlantic Canada in the War of 1812 | publisher = Oxford University Press| location = Oxford| year = 2017| isbn = 978-1-78694-923-3}}\n* {{cite book| first = W.| last = Klooster| title = The Dutch Moment: War, Trade, and Settlement in the Seventeenth-Century Atlantic World| publisher = Cornell University Press| location = Ithaca| year = 2016| isbn = 978-1-50170-667-7}}\n* {{cite journal |first= A. W.|last= Knauth|title=Prize Law Reconsidered|journal= Columbia Law Review|year=1946|volume=46 |issue=1 |pages=69-93| jstor=1118265}}\n* {{cite book| first = U.S.|last= Library of Congress| title = Statutes at Large, 38th Congress, 1st session, Chapter CLXXIV: An Act to regulate Prize Proceedings and the Distribution of Prize Money, and for other Purposes|  url = https://www.loc.gov/law/help/statutes-at-large/38th-congress/session-1/c38s1ch174.pdf}} \n* {{cite book| first = Christopher| last = Lloyd| title = The Navy and the Slave Trade: The Suppression of the African Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Century| publisher = Routledge| location = London| year = 2012| isbn = 978-0-71461-894-4}}\n* {{cite book| first = V. W.| last = Lunsford| title = Piracy and Privateering in the Golden Age Netherlands| publisher = Palgrave Macmillan| location = London| year = 1999| isbn = 978-1-34952-980-3}}\n* {{cite book| first = G.| last = Lushington| title = A Manual of Naval Prize Law (facsimile of the 1866 edition)| publisher = Creative Media Partners | location = London| year = 2005| isbn = 978-1-37925-646-5}}\n* {{cite book| first = Thomas| last = Malcomson| title 