 II. Sixth Congress, Chapter XXIII: An Act for the better government of the Navy of the United States| publisher = Charles C. Little & James Brown| location = Boston| year = 1845}}\n* {{cite journal |first= G. G. |last= Phillimore |title=Booty of War |journal= Journal of the Society of Comparative Legislation |year=1901|volume=3 |issue=2 |pages=214\u2013230| jstor=752066}}\n* {{cite book| first = N. A. M.| last = Rodger| title = The Command of the Ocean: A Naval History of Britain 1649\u20131815| publisher = W. W. Norton| location = New York| year = 2005| isbn = 0-393-06050-0| url = https://archive.org/details/commandofoceanna00rodg}}\n* {{cite book| first = G.| last = Symcox| title = The Crisis of French Sea Power, 1688\u20131697: From the Guerre d\u2019Escadre to the Guerre de Course| publisher = Marinus Nijhoff| location = The Hague| year = 1974| isbn = 978-9-40102-072-5}}\n* {{cite book| first = P. Q.| last = Wright| title = Prize Money 1649\u20131815| publisher = Project Gutenberg| location = Chicago| year = 1913| url = http://www.gutenberg.org/files/50814/50814-h/50814-h.htm}}\n* {{cite book| first = R-J.| last = Valan| title = Trait\u00e9 des prises: ou Principes de la jurisprudence fran\u00e7oise concernant les prises| publisher = J. Legier| location = La Rochelle| year = 1763}}\n* {{cite journal |first= J. P.|last= Van Niekerk |title=Of Naval Courts Martial and Prize Claims: Some Legal Consequences of Commodore Johnstone\u2019s secret mission to the Cape of Good Hope and the \u201cBattle\u201d of Saldanha Bay, 1781 (Part 2) |journal= Fundamina|year=2006|volume=22 |issue=1 |pages=118-157}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080621024038/http://www.hms.org.uk/nelsonsnavyprize.htm Nelson's Navy \u2013 Prize Money]\n\n{{Phaleristics}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Prize Money}}\n[[Category:History of the Royal Navy]]\n[[Category:Prize warfare]]\n[[Category:Naval warfarehristopher]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word 