{"title_page": "NLE Choppa", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|American rapper and songwriter}}\n{{distinguish|Choppa|text=}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = NLE Choppa\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| alias            = Baby Mexico, YNR Choppa\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|2002|11|1}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bookingagentinfo.com/celebrity/nle-choppa/|title=About NLE Choppa|publisher=Booking Agent Info|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Memphis, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], singer, songwriter, entertainer \n| background       = solo_singer\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = {{hlist||[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[trap music|trap]]}}\n| years_active     = 2018\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* No Love Entertainment\n* [[UnitedMasters]]\n* [[Warner Records|Warner]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[9lokkNine]]|[[Blueface]]|[[Bhad Bhabie]]|Shotta Fam|ATL Jacob|[[BlocBoy JB]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Bryson Lashun Potts'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/nle-choppa-announces-hes-officially-off-probation-news.92794.html|title=NLE Choppa Announces He's Officially Off Probation|last=Zidel|first=Alex|date=October 9, 2019|website=HotNewHipHop|url-status=live|access-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> (born November 1, 2002), better known as '''NLE Choppa''' (formerly known as '''YNR Choppa'''), is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, and entertainer based in [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. He is best known for his 2019 breakout single \"[[Shotta Flow]]\", which was [[Music recording certification|certified platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].\n\n==Early life==\nPotts was born to a [[Jamaicans | Jamaican]] mother and an [[African_Americans | African-American]] father.<ref name=\"Emerging\">{{cite news |last=Richards |first=M.T |date=January 23, 2020 |title=NLE Choppa: Young Memphis Rapper Tops Emerging Artist Charts  |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/memphis/nle-choppa-young-memphis-rapper-tops-emerging-artist-charts/Content?oid=22227329 |work=Memphis Flyer Newspaper |location=Memphis,Tennessee,USA |access-date=February 11, 2020 }}</ref> He was raised in [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]], Tennessee and attended the [[Cordova High School (Tennessee)|Cordova High School]] where he played [[basketball]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.prephoops.com/2018/10/4-observations-from-cordovas-open-gym-workout/|title=4 observations from Cordova's open gym workout|first=Courtney|last=Smith|publisher=Prep Hoops|date=October 22, 2018|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> He began [[Freestyle rap|freestyling]] with friends at the age of 14 and started taking music seriously at 15.<ref name=\"XXL\">{{cite news|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2019/02/nle-choppa-interview-the-break/|title=THE BREAK PRESENTS: NLE CHOPPA|first=Robby|last=Seabrook III|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=February 20, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNLE Choppa is the worlds worst rapper in the world he should delete all his music and stop making it because he is terrible.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nDuring an unspecified time, NLE Choppa served time at a [[Youth detention center|juvenile detention center]].<ref name=\"Mother\" /> He has never revealed what he went in for, but the artist has said his time at the detention center motivated him to turn his life around. In an episode of his YouTube series ''The Rise of NLE Choppa'', he said that being in juvenile helped him a lot and was an \"eye-opener\".<ref name=\"Mother\" />\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Title\n! Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Top Shotta''\n|\n* To be released\n* Label: No Love Entertainment\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!