 Moly\"<br />{{Small|(Blueface featuring NLE Choppa)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2020\n| \u2014 || 32\n| ''[[Find the Beat]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Grim Reapa Flow\"<br />{{Small|(30 Deep Grimeyy featuring NLE Choppa)}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| Non-album single\n|}\n\n===Other charted songs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of other charted songs, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ<br />Hot]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4797|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=December 28, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Matrix\"\n| 2019\n| 35\n| ''Cottonwood''\n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of non-single guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Other performer(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Dreams\"\n| rowspan=\"8\" | 2019\n| [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]], [[Juvenile (rapper)|Juvenile]]\n| ''Just Another Gangsta''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Double\"\n| [[Smokepurpp]]\n| ''Lost Planet''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Dance\"\n| HoodRich Pablo Juan, [[Key Glock]]\n| ''BLO: The Movie''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"100 or Better\"\n|[[Stunna 4 Vegas]]\n|''Big 4x''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Time to Shine\"\n| Young E.Z.\n| ''Time to Shine''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Hittas\"\n|[[Yella Beezy]]\n|''Baccend Beezy''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Poles\"\n|[[Quin Nfn]]\n|''4Nun''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"John Gotti\"\n|B. Lou\n|''Bow''\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n{{reflist|group=upper-roman}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:2002 births]]\n[[Category:African-American male rappers]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Memphis, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male musicians]]\n[[Category:Gangsta rappers]]\n[[Category:Crips]]\n[[Category:Warner Records artists]]\n[[Category:Southern hip hop musicians]]\n[[Category:American rappers of Jamaican descent]]\n[[Category:African-American male singers]]\n[[Category:Singers from Memphis, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|American rapper and songwriter}}\n{{distinguish|Choppa|text=}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = NLE Choppa\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| alias            = Baby Mexico, YNR Choppa\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|2002|11|1}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bookingagentinfo.com/celebrity/nle-choppa/|title=About NLE Choppa|publisher=Booking Agent Info|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Memphis, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], singer, songwriter, entertainer \n| background       = solo_singer\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = {{hlist||[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[trap music|trap]]}}\n| years_active     = 2018\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* No Love Entertainment\n* [[UnitedMasters]]\n* [[Warner Records|Warner]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[9lokkNine]]|[[Blueface]]|[[Bhad Bhabie]]|Shotta Fam|ATL Jacob|[[BlocBoy JB]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Bryson Lashun Potts'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/nle-choppa-announces-hes-officially-off-probation-news.92794.html|title=NLE Choppa Announces He's Officially Off Probation|last=Zidel|first=Alex|date=October 9, 2019|website=HotNewHipHop|url-status=live|access-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> (born November 1, 2002), better known as '''NLE Choppa''' (formerly known as '''YNR Choppa'''), is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, and entertainer based in [[Memphis, Tennessee]]. He is best known for his 2019 breakout single \"[[Shotta Flow]]\", which was [[Music recording certification|certified platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].\n\n==Early life==\nPotts was born to a [[Jamaicans | Jamaican]] mother and an [[African_Americans | African-American]] father.<ref name=\"Emerging\">{{cite news |last=Richards |first=M.T |date=January 23, 2020 |title=NLE Choppa: Young Memphis Rapper Tops Emerging Artist Charts  |url=https://www.memphisflyer.com/memphis/nle-choppa-young-memphis-rapper-tops-emerging-artist-charts/Content?oid=22227329 |work=Memphis Flyer Newspaper |location=Memphis,Tennessee,USA |access-date=February 11, 2020 }}</ref> He was raised in [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]], Tennessee and attended the [[Cordova High School (Tennessee)|Cordova High School]] where he played [[basketball]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.prephoops.com/2018/10/4-observations-from-cordovas-open-gym-workout/|title=4 observations from Cordova's open gym workout|first=Courtney|last=Smith|publisher=Prep Hoops|date=October 22, 2018|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> He began [[Freestyle rap|freestyling]] with friends at the age of 14 and started taking music seriously at 15.<ref name=\"XXL\">{{cite news|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2019/02/nle-choppa-interview-the-break/|title=THE BREAK PRESENTS: NLE CHOPPA|first=Robby|last=Seabrook III|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=February 20, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Musical career==\nNLE Choppa's manager is his mother, Angela Potts, who has been managing him since he started expressing an interest in rap music.<ref name=\"Mother\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/10/nle-choppa-everything-you-need-to-know|title=Everything You Need to Know About NLE Choppa|last=Jessica|first=McKinney|date=October 2, 2019|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|access-date=October 10, 2019}}</ref> He released his first song, \"No Love Anthem\", in February 2018 under the name YNR Choppa. On July 22, he released his debut [[mixtape]], ''No Love the Takeover''. In December, he appeared on \"No Chorus Pt''.'' 3\", a cypher-style song by his Shotta Fam collective. His opening verse and his dance moves in the accompanying music video made him stand out from the group, earning him an online buzz.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thedoublecup.com/nle-choppa|title=NLE Choppa: The Shotta Flow Rapper On The Come Up|publisher=The Double Cup|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://allhiphop.com/features/nle-choppa-the-16-year-old-viral-phenom-looks-to-take-the-game-over-LLsVrsqKTEiMPwt4uYgwuw/|title=NLE Choppa: The 16 Year Old Viral Phenom Looks To Take The Game Over|first=Chuck|last=Creekmur|publisher=All Hip-Hop|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter the surge of popularity, he released his breakout single \"[[Shotta Flow]]\" a week later. The video amassed 10 million views in a month.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.50303/title.nle-choppa-is-only-16-years-old-wants-to-make-millions-to-give-back#|title=Interview: NLE Choppa Is Only 16 Years Old & Wants To Make Millions To Give Back|first=Nunet|last=Clitandre|publisher=Hip-Hop DX|date=February 14, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> A few days after its release, ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' highlighted the track as its Song of the Day, praising his energetic delivery and adding that \"he hits a new dance move every time the camera cuts back to him\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://pitchfork.com/levels/nle-choppa-shotta-flow-new-song-listen/|title=The Ones: NLE Choppa's 'Shotta Flow'|last=Pierre|first=Alphonse|date=January 15, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref> The song entered the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in May 2019, debuting at number 96.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8509603/nle-choppa-hot-100-debut|title=NLE Choppa Scores First Billboard Hot 100 Entry With 'Shotta Flow'|first=Xander|last=Zellner|date=May 1, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> It later peaked at number 36. The official remix, featuring [[Blueface]], directed by [[Cole Bennett]], was released in June, shortly after the original song was certified platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/blueface-assists-nle-choppa-on-the-shotta-flow-remix-new-song.1983454.html|title=Blueface Assists NLE Choppa On The 'Shotta Flow' Remix|work=HotNewHipHop|date=June 20, 2019|accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February, he released the song's sequel, \"Shotta Flow 2\". The video received 20 million views within two months, prompting Carl Lamarre from [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] to say that his \"recent dominance has silenced any detractors\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8508389/nle-choppa-kiana-lede-luh-kel-chart-success|title=Emerging Hip-Hop: NLE Choppa, Kiana Lede & Luh Kel Make Noise With Latest Chart Moves|first=Carl|last=Lamarre|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=April 23, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> It was around this time that it was reported that Choppa had sparked a bidding war between a handful of top record labels, with bids reaching a reported $3&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8498052/memphis-rapper-nle-choppa-label-bidding-war|title=Memphis Rapper NLE Choppa Sparks $3 Million Label Bidding War: Exclusive|first=Tatiana|last=Cirisano|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 13, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> He turned these offers down, however, to instead sign with the independent distribution company, [[UnitedMasters]], while keeping his master recordings and publishing.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8498476/nle-choppa-turned-down-a-3-million-record-deal-partner-united-masters|title=Why 16-Year-Old Rapper NLE Choppa Turned Down a $3 Million Record Deal to Partner With UnitedMasters: Exclusive|first=Tatiana|last=Cirisano|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> In March, he released a new single called \"Capo\", with the music video debuting on [[Worldstarhiphop]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldstarhiphop.com/videos/video.php?v=wshhDLd6u681uT26QOsx|title=NLE Choppa \u2013 Capo|website=WORLDSTARHIPHOP|accessdate=November 16, 2019}}</ref> Also in March, he was featured on [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]] and [[Juvenile (rapper)|Juvenile]]'s song \"Dreams\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/birdman-and-juvenile-boost-nle-choppa-with-dope-new-single-dreams-new-song.1982306.html|title=Birdman & Juvenile Boost NLE Choppa With Dope New Single \"Dreams\"|first=Alex|last=Zidel|publisher=HotNewHipHop|date=March 14, 2019|accessdate=May 9, 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, NLE released another single called \"Birdboy\", produced by SGULL.\n\nIn May, Choppa released a new single, \"Blocc Is Hot\", produced by ATL Jacob.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/music/news/nle-choppa-26-atl-jacob-talk-new-single-blocc-is-hot-wanting-to-get-lil-wayne-on-the-remix/ar-AAARmTG|title=NLE Choppa & ATL Jacob Talk New Single 'Blocc Is Hot,' Wanting to Get Lil Wayne on the Remix|first=Michael|last=Saponara|publisher=MSN|date=May 3, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> It was made as a tribute to his favorite childhood rapper, [[Lil Wayne]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/nle-choppa-returns-on-blocc-is-hot-new-song.1982854.html|title=NLE Choppa Returns On 'Blocc Is Hot'|first=Milca|last=Pierre|publisher=HotNewHipHop|date=May 4, 2019|accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref> A few days later, he made his music festival debut by performing at the [[Beale Street Music Festival]] in Memphis. Bob Mehr of [[The Commercial Appeal]] praised his act, saying that he \"did much to seize the opportunity on the big stage in his hometown\" and that \"his career is likely to see plenty more memorable Memphis moments.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.commercialappeal.com/story/entertainment/music/2019/05/05/nle-choppa-memphis-may-beale-street-music-festival/3655352002/|title=Memphis rapper NLE Choppa brings the party to Beale Street Music Festival|first=Bob|last=Mehr|publisher=[[The Commercial Appeal]]|date=May 5, 2019|accessdate=May 9, 2019}}</ref> On June 14, 2019, he released the single, \"Free Youngboy\", produced by CashMoneyAP. The music video has achieved over 19 million views on YouTube. The title of this song is a reference to rapper [[NBA YoungBoy]], who was arrested for shooting and because he violated his parole. This song was the first release from his own label No Love Entertainment (NLE), which he launched in partnership with [[Warner Records]].<ref name=\"NoLoveLabel\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8519758/nle-choppa-launches-own-label-warner-records|title=NLE Choppa Launches Own Label in Partnership with Warner Records|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=July 12, 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=July 30, 2019}}</ref> According to [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] magazine, No Love Entertainment is slated to release new music from NLE Choppa.<ref name=\"NoLoveLabel\" /> On September 13, 2019, NLE Choppa released a new single titled \"[[Camelot (NLE Choppa song)|Camelot]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/09/nle-choppa-camelot-video|title=Watch NLE Choppa's Cole Bennett-Directed Video for \"Camelot\"|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|access-date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> The song peaked at number 37 in the US, becoming his second Top 40 hit, following \"Shotta Flow\".<ref name=\"Hot 100\" /> \n\nOn December 20, 2019, NLE Choppa released his debut [[extended play]] titled ''[[Cottonwood (EP)|Cottonwood]].''<ref name=\"Cottonwood\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/12/nle-choppa-cottonwood-stream|title=NLE Choppa Drops 'Cottonwood' Project|last=Price|first=Joe|date=December 20, 2019|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|access-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> The EP, named after the area he grew up in,<ref name=\"Success\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/12/nle-choppa-cottonwood-ep-interview|title=NLE Choppa Spent Years Praying For Success\u2014Now He Wants to Change Everyone's Lives|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|date=December 13, 2019|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|access-date=December 20, 2019}}</ref> features the previously released singles \"Side\" and his breakthrough hit \"[[Shotta Flow]]\". To accompany the release of ''Cottonwood'', a short film of the same name was released.<ref name=\"Cottonwood\" /> NLE Choppa's debut album is set for release in the first quarter of 2020.<ref name=\"Emerging\" />\n\n==Personal life==\n\nDuring an unspecified time, NLE Choppa served time at a [[Youth detention center|juvenile detention center]].<ref name=\"Mother\" /> He has never revealed what he went in for, but the artist has said his time at the detention center motivated him to turn his life around. In an episode of his YouTube series ''The Rise of NLE Choppa'', he said that being in juvenile helped him a lot and was an \"eye-opener\".<ref name=\"Mother\" />\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Title\n! Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Top Shotta''\n|\n* To be released\n* Label: No Love Entertainment\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref>{{cite tweet|user=billboardcharts|number=1211711000686288901|title=Debuts on this week's #Billboard200 (1/2)|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US<br />R&B/HH]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/nle-choppa/chart-history/BLP|title=NLE Choppa Chart History: Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/nle-choppa/chart-history/CNA|title=NLE Choppa Chart History: Canadian Albums Chart|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Cottonwood (EP)|Cottonwood]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/12/nle-choppa-cottonwood-ep-interview|title=NLE Choppa Spent Years Praying For Success\u2014Now He Wants to Change Everyone's Lives|first=Jessica|last=McKinney|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=December 13, 2019|accessdate=December 13, 2019}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: December 20, 2019\n* Label: No Love Entertainment\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n| 57 || 20 || 64\n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''No Love the Takeover''<br />{{small|(as YNR Choppa)}}\n|\n* Released: July 22, 2018<ref name=\"no-love\">{{cite web |title=No Love Take Over by YNR Choppa |url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/no-love-take-over/1416664602 |via= Apple Music |accessdate= September 16, 2019}}</ref>\n* Label: No Love Entertainment\n* Format: Digital download, streaming\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as a solo artist, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:13em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"