{"title_page": "Riley (given name)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Given Name Revised\n| name = Rileigh, Riley\n| image=\n| imagesize=\n| caption=\n| pronunciation= {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|r|a\u026a|l|i}} {{respell|RY|lee}}\n| gender = [[unisex name|unisex]] \n| meaning = \"Valiant, Courageous, Lively, Brave, Fiery, rye clearing\" Oxford Dictionary: Noun. \"a luxurious or carefree existence\" \n| origin = [[Irish Gaelic]]\n| related names = Rylee, Ryleigh, Rylie, Reilly, Reily, Rheilly, Rilie\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Riley''' is a [[unisex]] given name, which first appeared as ''Raghallach'', which was originated on a man who died in the [[Battle of Clontarf]]. Its source gives its meaning as \"valiant\".<ref>Rosenkrantz, Linda, and Satran, Pamela Redmond (2007). ''Baby Name Bible''. St. Martin's Griffin. {{ISBN|978-0-312-35220-2}}</ref> Meaning \"Valiant, Courageous, Lively, Brave, rye clearing\" Oxford definition: Noun. \"a luxurious or carefree existence.\" \n\nUntil the 1990s and early 2000s, Riley in the United States was primarily a boy's name. However in 2017, it was the 25th most popular girl's name, and the 253rd most popular boy's name.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssa.gov/cgi-bin/babyname.cgi|title=Popular Baby Names|website=www.ssa.gov|accessdate=Aug 12, 2019}}</ref> In the UK, Riley is primarily a boy's name, being the fortieth most popular name given to baby boys in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2017/sep/20/olivia-oliver-2016-top-baby-names-england-and-wales|title=Olivia and Oliver were 2016's top baby names in England and Wales|date=Sep 20, 2017|accessdate=Aug 12, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\nThe surname's first variant is [[\u00d3 Raghallaigh]] (Descendant of/Of Raghallach) which was later adapted in [[English Language|English]] as [[O'Reilly]] which itself has been anglicised into \"Reilly\". The surname \"Riley\" is a translated version of Reilly; which evolved over time.\nIt currently is #8 in [[England]] and [[Wales]], #9 in [[Northern Ireland]], #15 in [[Scotland]], #30 in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]], #64 in [[Canada]], and #198 in the [[Netherlands]]{{citation_needed|date=April 2019}}.\n\n==People with first name \"Riley\"==\n* [[Riley Armstrong (ice hockey)]] (1984\u2013)\n* [[Riley Armstrong (musician)]] (1976\u2013)\n* [[Riley P. Bechtel]] (1952\u2013), American businessman\n* [[Riley A. Bender]] (1890\u20131973), American businessman and politician\n* [[Riley Biggs]] (1900\u20131971), American football player\n* [[Riley Breckenridge]] (1975\u2013), American musician\n* [[Riley Brett]] (1895\u20131982), American race car driver\n* [[Riley Chamberlin]] (1852\u20131917), American silent film actor\n* [[Riley Cooper]] (1987\u2013) American football player\n* [[Riley Cote]] (1982\u2013) , Canadian ice hockey player\n* [[Riley Darnell]] (1940\u2013), American Secretary of State of Tennessee\n* [[Riley Dolezal]] (born 1985), American javelin thrower\n* [[Riley Ferguson]] (1995\u2013), American football player\n* [[Riley Gardner]] (1921\u20132007), American psychologist\n* [[Riley Keough]] (born 1989), American actress and model\n* [[Riley B. King]] ([[B.B. King]]) (1925\u20132015), American blues guitarist and singer-songwriter\n* [[Riley Knight]] (1995\u2013), Australian rules football player\n* [[Riley Martin]] (1946\u20132015), American author\n* [[Riley Matheson]] (1914\u20131987), American football player\n* [[Riley Mattson]] (1938\u2013), American football player\n* [[Riley McCusker]] (2001\u2013), American gymnast\n* [[Riley Franklin McConnell]] (1884\u20131940), American recipient of the Navy Cross\n* [[Riley Nash]] (1989\u2013), Canadian ice hockey player\n* [[Riley Dobi Noel]] (1972\u20132004), American murderer\n* [[Riley O'Neill]] (1985\u2013), Canadian soccer player\n* [[Riley Odoms]] (1950\u2013), American football player\n* [[Riley L. Pitts]] (1937\u20131967), first African-American officer to be awarded the Medal of Honor\n* [[Riley Puckett]] (1894\u20131946), American musician\n* [[Riley Reid]] (1991\u2013), American pornographic actress\n* [[Riley Reiff]] (1988\u2013), American football player\n* [[Riley Ridley]] (born 1996), American football player\n* [[Riley Salmon]] (1976\u2013), American volleyball player\n* [[Riley Skinner]] (1986\u2013), American college football player\n* [[Riley Smith]] (born 1978), American actor\n* [[Riley Smith (American football)]] (1911\u20131999)\n* [[Riley E. Stratton]] (1823\u20131866), American attorney and judge\n* [[Riley Swanson]] (born 1984), American attorney and judge\n* [[Riley Thomson]] (1912\u20131960), American animator\n* [[Riley Voelkel]] (born 1990), American actress\n* [[Riley Wallace]] (born 1941), American basketball coach\n* [[Riley Ware]] (born 1962), American football player\n* [[Riley J. Wilson]] (1871\u20131946), American attorney and legislator\n\n==Fictional characters==\n* [[Riley Andersen]], a character in the movie ''Inside Out''\n* [[Riley Biers]], a character in the ''Twilight'' books\n* [[Riley Dawson]], character in the television series ''Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles''\n* [[Riley Finn]], character in the television series ''Buffy the Vampire Slayer''\n* [[Riley Freeman]], character in the animated television series ''The Boondocks''\n* [[Riley Parker]], a character on ''[[Neighbours]]''\n* [[Riley Poole]], character in the ''National Treasure'' franchise\n* [[Riley Stavros]], a character in ''Degrassi: The Next Generation''\n* Riley Davis, a character in the television series ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'', 2016 reboot version\n* [[Riley Blue]], a character in the [[Netflix]] original series '' [[Sense8]]''\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{given name}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Riley (Given Name)}}\n[[Category:English given names]]\n[[Category:English unisex given names]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Given Name Revised\n| name = Rileigh, Riley\n| image=\n| imagesize=\n| caption=\n| pronunciation= {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|r|a\u026a|l|i}} {{respell|RY|lee}}\n| gender = [[unisex name|unisex]] \n| meaning = \"Valiant, Courageous, Lively, Brave, Fiery, rye clearing\" Oxford Dictionary: Noun. \"a luxurious or carefree existence\" \n| origin = [[Irish Gaelic]]\n| related names = Rylee, Ryleigh, Rylie, Reilly, Reily, Rheilly, Rilie\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Riley''' is a [[unisex]] given name, which first appeared as ''Raghallach'', which was originated on a man who died in the [[Battle of Clontarf]]. Its source gives its meaning as \"valiant\".<ref>Rosenkrantz, Linda, and Satran, Pamela Redmond (2007). ''Baby Name Bible''. St. Martin's Griffin. {{ISBN|978-0-312-35220-2}}</ref> Meaning \"Valiant, Courageous, Lively, Brave, rye clearing\" Oxford definition: Noun. \"a luxurious or carefree existence.\" \n\nUntil the 90's and early 2000's Riley in the United States was primarily a boy's name. However in 2017, it was the twenty-fifth most popular girl's name, and the 253rd most popular boy's name.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssa.gov/cgi-bin/babyname.cgi|title=Popular Baby Names|website=www.ssa.gov|accessdate=Aug 12, 2019}}</ref> In the UK, Riley is primarily a boy's name, being the fortieth most popular name given to baby boys in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2017/sep/20/olivia-oliver-2016-top-baby-names-england-and-wales|title=Olivia and Oliver were 2016's top baby names in England and Wales|date=Sep 20, 2017|accessdate=Aug 12, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\nThe surname's first variant is [[\u00d3 Raghallaigh]] (Descendant of/Of Raghallach) which was later adapted in [[English Language|English]] as [[O'Reilly]] which itself has been anglicised into \"Reilly\". The surname \"Riley\" is a translated version of Reilly; which evolved over time.\nIt currently is #8 in [[England]] and [[Wales]], #9 in [[Northern Ireland]], #15 in [[Scotland]], #30 in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]], #64 in [[Canada]], and #198 in the [[Netherlands]]{{citation_needed|date=April 2019}}.\n\n==